---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";
import CTABand from "../components/CTABand.astro";
import { withBase } from "../lib/base";

const pillars = [
  {
    title: "Spiritual",
    icon: "m3.55 19.09l1.41 1.41l1.8-1.79l-1.42-1.42M12 6c-3.31 0-6 2.69-6 6s2.69 6 6 6s6-2.69 6-6c0-3.32-2.69-6-6-6m8 7h3v-2h-3m-2.76 7.71l1.8 1.79l1.41-1.41l-1.79-1.8M20.45 5l-1.41-1.4l-1.8 1.79l1.42 1.42M13 1h-2v3h2M6.76 5.39L4.96 3.6L3.55 5l1.79 1.81zM1 13h3v-2H1m12 9h-2v3h2",
    body: "Our first focus is helping you build a personal, intuitive connection with your Creator. This is the cornerstone of recovering from addiction and living with real balance. Through your own spiritual insights, the study of wisdom traditions, and the search for self-knowledge, you begin to find your purpose and align your life with it. Discovering that purpose, and living it, is both the foundation and the goal of our program.",
    points: [
      "Guided spiritual work with sacrament",
      "Integration of spiritual traditions",
      "Study of spiritual philosophy",
      "Instruction in spiritual practice",
      "Bringing spirituality into daily life",
    ],
  },
  {
    title: "Mental",
    icon: "M21.33 12.91c.09 1.55-.62 3.04-1.89 3.95l.77 1.49c.23.45.26.98.06 1.45c-.19.47-.58.84-1.06 1l-.79.25a1.69 1.69 0 0 1-1.86-.55L14.44 18c-.89-.15-1.73-.53-2.44-1.1c-.5.15-1 .23-1.5.23c-.88 0-1.76-.27-2.5-.79c-.53.16-1.07.23-1.62.22c-.79.01-1.57-.15-2.3-.45a4.1 4.1 0 0 1-2.43-3.61c-.08-.72.04-1.45.35-2.11c-.29-.75-.32-1.57-.07-2.33C2.3 7.11 3 6.32 3.87 5.82c.58-1.69 2.21-2.82 4-2.7c1.6-1.5 4.05-1.66 5.83-.37c.42-.11.86-.17 1.3-.17c1.36-.03 2.65.57 3.5 1.64c2.04.53 3.5 2.35 3.58 4.47c.05 1.11-.25 2.2-.86 3.13c.07.36.11.72.11 1.09m-5-1.41c.57.07 1.02.5 1.02 1.07a1 1 0 0 1-1 1h-.63c-.32.9-.88 1.69-1.62 2.29c.25.09.51.14.77.21c5.13-.07 4.53-3.2 4.53-3.25a2.59 2.59 0 0 0-2.69-2.49a1 1 0 0 1-1-1a1 1 0 0 1 1-1c1.23.03 2.41.49 3.33 1.3c.05-.29.08-.59.08-.89c-.06-1.24-.62-2.32-2.87-2.53c-1.25-2.96-4.4-1.32-4.4-.4c-.03.23.21.72.25.75a1 1 0 0 1 1 1c0 .55-.45 1-1 1c-.53-.02-1.03-.22-1.43-.56c-.48.31-1.03.5-1.6.56c-.57.05-1.04-.35-1.07-.9a.97.97 0 0 1 .88-1.1c.16-.02.94-.14.94-.77c0-.66.25-1.29.68-1.79c-.92-.25-1.91.08-2.91 1.29C6.75 5 6 5.25 5.45 7.2C4.5 7.67 4 8 3.78 9c1.08-.22 2.19-.13 3.22.25c.5.19.78.75.59 1.29c-.19.52-.77.78-1.29.59c-.73-.32-1.55-.34-2.3-.06c-.32.27-.32.83-.32 1.27c0 .74.37 1.43 1 1.83c.53.27 1.12.41 1.71.4q-.225-.39-.39-.81a1.038 1.038 0 0 1 1.96-.68c.4 1.14 1.42 1.92 2.62 2.05c1.37-.07 2.59-.88 3.19-2.13c.23-1.38 1.34-1.5 2.56-1.5m2 7.47l-.62-1.3l-.71.16l1 1.25zm-4.65-8.61a1 1 0 0 0-.91-1.03c-.71-.04-1.4.2-1.93.67c-.57.58-.87 1.38-.84 2.19a1 1 0 0 0 1 1c.57 0 1-.45 1-1c0-.27.07-.54.23-.76c.12-.1.27-.15.43-.15c.55.03 1.02-.38 1.02-.92",
    body: "Real well-being starts with getting your own mind back. Our thoughts shape our reality, so we lean on meditation and mindfulness as core tools for healing and building healthier mental habits. When you learn to quiet the mind and settle your nervous system, you can make choices that serve your goals instead of ones that lead to harm. From there, a more intentional and balanced life becomes possible.",
    points: [
      "Meditation",
      "Mindfulness",
      "Self-reflection",
      "Self-coaching",
    ],
  },
  {
    title: "Emotional",
    icon: "m12.1 18.55l-.1.1l-.11-.1C7.14 14.24 4 11.39 4 8.5C4 6.5 5.5 5 7.5 5c1.54 0 3.04 1 3.57 2.36h1.86C13.46 6 14.96 5 16.5 5c2 0 3.5 1.5 3.5 3.5c0 2.89-3.14 5.74-7.9 10.05M16.5 3c-1.74 0-3.41.81-4.5 2.08C10.91 3.81 9.24 3 7.5 3C4.42 3 2 5.41 2 8.5c0 3.77 3.4 6.86 8.55 11.53L12 21.35l1.45-1.32C18.6 15.36 22 12.27 22 8.5C22 5.41 19.58 3 16.5 3",
    body: "Healing from trauma takes time, but you don't have to take the first steps alone. Addiction often grows from feelings and wounds we've buried, so in both group and private sessions with skilled practitioners, we help you begin to surface and face them. Alongside your peers and coaches, you practice honest communication and authentic self-expression every day. Those habits are the ground for lasting emotional health and stronger relationships, and you carry the tools home with you.",
    points: [
      "Group and private therapeutic sessions",
      "Energetic clearing",
      "Emotional regulation",
      "Healthy communication skills",
    ],
  },
  {
    title: "Physical",
    icon: "M13.5 5.5c1.09 0 2-.92 2-2a2 2 0 0 0-2-2c-1.11 0-2 .88-2 2c0 1.08.89 2 2 2M9.89 19.38l1-4.38L13 17v6h2v-7.5l-2.11-2l.61-3A7.3 7.3 0 0 0 19 13v-2c-1.91 0-3.5-1-4.31-2.42l-1-1.58c-.4-.62-1-1-1.69-1c-.31 0-.5.08-.81.08L6 8.28V13h2V9.58l1.79-.7L8.19 17l-4.9-1l-.4 2z",
    body: "Addiction and the pace of modern life lead many people to neglect the body. Most arrive needing help to cleanse, balance, and recalibrate. We build new habits around you, with a personal approach to movement, diet, and sleep that you can actually sustain. Holistic care rounds it out, from acupuncture to herbalists who suggest herbs and dietary changes to support your healing.",
    points: [
      "Fitness and nutrition",
      "Acupuncture and herbalism",
      "Yoga and other movement",
      "Massage and somatic bodywork",
    ],
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Our Approach · Casa da Nova Vida"
  description="We treat addiction at the root by healing the whole self: spirit, mind, emotions, and body."
>
  <!-- ===================== HERO ===================== -->
  <PageHero
    eyebrow="Our Approach"
    title="Healing the whole self"
    image="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1518495973542-4542c06a5843?auto=format&fit=crop&w=2000&q=80"
    imageAlt="Sunlight through the branches of a great tree"
  />

  <!-- ===================== LEAD ===================== -->
  <section class="px-6 py-16 lg:px-10 lg:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
      <p class="eyebrow">Our belief</p>
      <p class="mt-5 font-display text-2xl leading-[1.4] text-cocoa sm:text-3xl">
        To find healing, you have to embrace a <span class="text-pine">New Life</span> in
        every part of yourself: spiritually, mentally, emotionally, and
        physically.
      </p>
      <p class="mx-auto mt-6 max-w-xl leading-relaxed text-cocoa">
        Addiction touches the whole person, so we treat the whole person. These
        four parts are not separate. We tend to them together.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== FOUR PILLARS ===================== -->
  <section class="border-y border-sand bg-cream px-6 py-20 lg:px-10 lg:py-28">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-2xl text-center">
        <p class="eyebrow">The four pillars</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl text-pine sm:text-4xl">Four parts, one path</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="mt-14 grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-2">
        {
          pillars.map((p) => (
            <div class="rounded-3xl border border-sand bg-linen p-8">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-4">
                <div class="flex h-12 w-12 flex-none items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-gradient-to-br from-cream to-sage/40 text-pine ring-1 ring-sand">
                  <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="h-6 w-6" fill="currentColor" aria-hidden="true">
                    <path d={p.icon} />
                  </svg>
                </div>
                <h3 class="text-xl text-forest">{p.title}</h3>
              </div>
              <p class="mt-5 leading-relaxed text-cocoa">{p.body}</p>
              <ul class="mt-5 space-y-2.5">
                {p.points.map((pt) => (
                  <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-cocoa">
                    <span class="mt-1.5 h-1.5 w-1.5 flex-none rounded-full bg-moss" />
                    <span class="leading-relaxed">{pt}</span>
                  </li>
                ))}
              </ul>
            </div>
          ))
        }
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== HARM REDUCTION ===================== -->
  <section class="px-6 py-20 lg:px-10 lg:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[0.8fr_1.2fr] lg:items-center lg:gap-16">
      <div>
        <p class="eyebrow">Our philosophy of care</p>
        <h2 class="mt-3 text-3xl text-pine sm:text-4xl">Harm reduction</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="space-y-5 leading-relaxed text-cocoa">
        <p>
          We embrace a harm reduction philosophy because it is honest about how
          healing actually happens. Everyone's journey is different, and change
          rarely runs in a straight line. Instead of enforcing rigid
          expectations, we make space for honesty, agency, and self-awareness.
        </p>
        <p>
          That means room to build trust with yourself and others while you
          explore lasting changes at a pace you can keep. By meeting you where
          you are, without judgment, we help lay the ground for real, long-term
          healing rooted in choice, connection, and community.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ===================== QUOTE ===================== -->
  <section class="bg-cream px-6 py-16 lg:px-10 lg:py-24">
    <div class="mx-auto grid max-w-6xl items-center gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-16">
      <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-[1.75rem] shadow-lg">
        <img
          src={withBase("/images/photos/life/cross.jpg")}
          alt="A wooden cross draped with prayer beads on the table, guests resting nearby"
          class="h-72 w-full object-cover sm:h-96 lg:h-[28rem]"
          loading="lazy"
        />
      </div>
      <figure class="text-center lg:text-left">
        <blockquote class="font-display text-2xl leading-relaxed text-pine sm:text-3xl">
          “Love without firmness<br />Is a fire without heat<br />It is a weak
          thought<br />And a body without worth”
        </blockquote>
        <figcaption class="mt-6 text-sm uppercase tracking-[0.18em] text-stone">
          Padrinho Sebastião
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="py-20 lg:py-28"><CTABand /></div>
</Layout>
